@NODE "FEATURES"     "Features"
                                                                     
     + Auto updates, so you can watch people logging on/off and moving.
     + Tells you when a New User is logging on unlike other WHo`s
     + You can type WHO for a full WHO or type WH for a quick WHo!
     + You can ask people to chat while using the Program
     + You can send/receive OLM`s in the Program without quitting.
     + You can change your WHo Banner while in the Program.
     + You can hide from people and they wont know your there.
     + You can skip Idle ports in the program by using CNet's Config 
     + You can specify ports to watch, not just all of them.
     + It'ss 100% Compatible with CNet 4.11-4.24  and CNet 3.05c
     + Has an easy to use Config Editor.
     + Easy to use for sysops, and especially for new Users.                        
     + Has a very configurable look, you can change colours etc.
     + Looks Nice.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "FILES"        "Files in the archive"
     
     In this archive you should have the following main files in a directory
     call ProWho. (Excluding the adverts of cause:)

     AFD-COPYRIGHT         7266 bytes - AFD Copyright Notice
     ProWho.doc           13907 bytes - The ASCII documentation!
     ProWho.guide         18206 bytes - Your looking at it :)!
     ProWho2.rexx         24833 bytes - The main rexx file
     ProConfig2.rexx      17496 bytes - The config editor
     Snapshots              Directory - This directory contains snapshots 

     If these files do not have the correct names/sizes, please don't run them
     and report them to me immediately!

@ENDNODE

@NODE "INSTALLATION" "Installation"

1.   Copy the programs ProWho2.rexx and ProConfig2.rexx to a directory.
                         (Usually Pfiles:ProWho/)

        @{"Click Here to copy files auto-matically to Pfiles:ProWho/" SYSTEM "Copy #? PFiles:ProWho"}

2.   Next you must load up the file BBStext (Which is located in your CNet:)
     into your favourite editor and change lines 42 and 62 so that they 
     read:-

Line #42 : Add this to the    End    "#0Pfiles:ProWho/ProWho2.rexx NEW}"
Line #62 : Add this to the Beginning "#0Pfiles:ProWho/ProWho2.rexx NEW}"
                                      ^         ^-[ This is the path you choose ]
                                      `-----------[      This is a CTRL+Q       ]

     Then Save 'n Exit.

                @{"Click here to choose your favourite Editor!" SYSTEM "SetEnv PWHO `RequestFile C:`"}

              @{"Click here to load CNet:BBSText into an Editor!" SYSTEM "$PWHO CNet:BBSText"}

3.   Next you must load up the file BBSMenu (Which is located in your CNet:)
     into your favourite editor and perform the following changes under menu
     "2; Available Everywhere"

 a.  Find the line which says WHo on it, once found change it to say
     !WHo if not already done.

 b.  Goto the bottom of menu #2 and add these commands:-

     WH              |       #0 Pfiles:ProWho/ProWho2.rexx   }
     WHO             |       #0 Pfiles:ProWho/ProWho2.rexx   }
     WHOCONFIG `31-  |       #0 Pfiles:ProWho/ProConfig2.rexx }
                ^            ^          ^[ This is the path you choose ]
                |            `-----------[      This is a CTRL+Q       ]
                `----[    This allows only sysops to run the command   ] 

     Then Save 'n Exit.

              @{"Click here to load CNet:BBSMenu into an Editor!" SYSTEM "$PWHO CNet:BBSMenu"}

4.   Then you have to load the file "Systext:new/comp" into your favourite
     editor and this line to the beginning 
     
          #0 Pfiles:ProWho/ProWho2.rexx NEW NewUser}
          ^          ^--------------[ You must know what this is by now :)
          `-------------------------[ And this :)

     Then Save 'n Exit.

            @{"Click here to load Systext:new/comp into an Editor!" SYSTEM "$PWHO Systext:new/comp"}

5.   Go to your control panel and type Right Amiga + T or use your mouse
     to do a Text/Menu Reload!

6.   Now that the hard bit is out of the way, you can configure this 
     Excellent tool:). 

     Login to your BBS and once at the main menu type "WHOCONFIG", this will
     load a Vis Ed type screen, you should configure all of the parts to
     suit your needs.  You can now configure the colours and some of the
     wording in the Who program.

7.   After you have successfully configured Professional Who, type WHO and
     See if it works, if not then you have done something wrong.  Remember
     that WH does a quick who.  If you have futhur problems, please email
     me telling me what goes wrong.

8.   Tell yours users about this program and send me (Trebor) loads of money:)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "UPGRADE3"     "Upgrading 1.9 --> 2.1 [Public Release]"

     To upgrade from ProWho V1.9 to ProWho V2.1, just follow the steps.

                @{"Click here to choose your favourite Editor!" SYSTEM "SetEnv PWHO `RequestFile C:`"}

1.   Delete the all the files in the old ProWho directory

       @{"Click Here to delete files auto-matically in Pfiles:ProWho/" SYSTEM "Delete PFiles:ProWho"}

2.   Copy files ProWho2.rexx, and ProConfig2.rexx to your default directory 
     for ProWho (Usually Pfiles:ProWho/).

       @{"Click Here to copy files auto-matically to Pfiles:ProWho/" SYSTEM "Copy #? PFiles:ProWho"}

3.   Run the conversion program (Update2.rexx) from CNet and you will be
     ready to go apart from the below ;>

4.   Load CNet:BBSMenu into your favourite editor and locate the lines with
     WHO, WHo, WHOCONFIG on and change the names from ProWho.rexx to
     ProWho2.rexx, and also change ProConfig.rexx to ProConfig2.rexx

              @{"Click here to load CNet:BBSMenu into an Editor!" SYSTEM "$PWHO CNet:BBSMenu"}

5.   Next you must load up the file BBStext into your favourite editor and 
     change lines 42 and 62 so that they read instead of ProWho.rexx

Line #42 : Add this to the    End    "#0Pfiles:ProWho/ProWho2.rexx NEW}"
Line #62 : Add this to the Beginning "#0Pfiles:ProWho/ProWho2.rexx NEW}"
                                      ^         ^-[ This is the path you choose ]
                                      `-----------[      This is a CTRL+Q       ]

              @{"Click here to load CNet:BBSText into an Editor!" SYSTEM "$PWHO CNet:BBSText"}

6.   Also load the file "Systext:new/comp" into your favourite editor and 
     make sure you change it to ProWho2.rexx like below.
     
          #0 Pfiles:ProWho/ProWho2.rexx NEW NewUser}
          ^          ^--------------[ You must know what this is by now :)
          `-------------------------[ And this :)

            @{"Click here to load Systext:new/comp into an Editor!" SYSTEM "$PWHO Systext:new/comp"}

     ** DONT FORGET TO DO A TEXT/MENU RELOAD AND TO TRY OUT THE NEW **
                         ** CONFIG PROGRAM **

     ** ALSO REMEMBER THAT THE KEYFILE HAS CHANGED, YOU MUST EMAIL ME **
                          ** FOR A NEW ONE **

7.   That`s it, you have now installed Professional Who V2.0, if you find 
     any bugs you know what to do:).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HISTORY"      "History of Professional Who"

     V2.1     04/05/97   Re-Written Olm Routine to use new time stamping 
                         which was very complicated and took over 2 hours 
                         with help from Ken Hood.  Fixed little bugs.

     V2.0h    27/04/97   Fixed bug in Be Right Back when it was Unregistered
                         And fixed Olming not to work at all if its 
                         Unregistered.

     V2.0g    25/04/97   Getusers have changed for CNet 4.26d, so had to
                         put the new ones in, also Olming Routine has changed
                         so it has a time stamp now, not fixed for ProWho
                         but better than before!
                         
     V2.0f    04/04/97   Fixed bug with the Super user flag, and sum colour
			 problems.

     V2.0e    01/04/97   Finished NEW config editor, now able to change the
			 all the main Colours in the Who program, and also
                         Works fully with CNet 4.26.

     V2.0c    23/03/97   Started working on NEW config editor, alowing you to
                         change colours, etc!

     V2.0b    17/02/97   Changeg Some getusers to work with the getuser shift!

     V2.0a    01/01/97   Released to Beta testers, to find Bugs!

     V2.0     07/12/96   Added Be Right Back option, and changed some wording.
                                                                            
     V1.9     24/10/96   Now works 100% with CNet V4.24, there was yet another
                         bug with hiding/muffling, not  my fault, it was CNet's:)
                         Also added new feature for port arguments, i.e.
                         Who 1 3-4 10, would only show Ports 1,3,4,and 10.
                         And for people with CNet V4.2x i have added the Super
                         User flag.

     V1.8     05/09/96   Now works 100% with Cnet V4.21, there was a bug with
                         hiding/muffling, not my fault, it was CNet's :)

     V1.7     01/09/96   Public Release and uploaded to Aminet!
                         Changed olming routine, and now looks nicer and can
                         handle upto 380 characters (ThanX to Duval).
                         Also allowed the program to go over 10 ports (For you
                         Lucky people out there with the money:))

     V1.6b    28/07/96   Optimised Config editor to make it a bit faster 
                         and Fixed Hide, Muffle command on CNet 4.11+.
                         Should now be 100% Compatible with CNet 4.11+ and
                         CNet 3.05c!

     V1.5b    24/07/96   Fixed bug in olm routine, and also added newuser
                         part.

     V1.4b    23/06/96   Added Vis Editor look config editor!

     V1.1b    26/05/96   Made the program CNet 4.1xx compatible!

     V1.0b    15/03/96   Total Rewrite, to make it faster!

     V0.7b    19/01/96   Made the program receive OLM's instead of quitting
                                                                            
     V0.6b    05/01/96   Made ports only refresh if something happens
                         (Suggestion by Duval and Bob)

     V0.5b    02/01/96   Added keyfile

     V0.2b    26/12/95   Hide, Muffle command was added.

     V0.1b    05/07/95   First Release.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "FUTURE"       "For the Future"

     To allow you to see what file is been uploaded/downloaded on another port
     and time to completion, while been in the Who!

@ENDNODE
